This paper is about improving the robustness of machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of new approaches to improve models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the submitted systems using automatic evaluation metrics, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions a qualitative analysis of the submitted systems, which could involve computer vision techniques and therefore fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
